profileText: A Representative from Ohio; born in Willard, Huron County, Ohio, October 25, 1877; educated in the public schools of Norwalk, Ohio; was graduated from the law department of Baldwin-Wallace University, Berea, Ohio, in 1901; was admitted to the bar the same year and commenced practice in Sandusky, Ohio; served as city solicitor of Sandusky 1903-1909; judge of the common pleas court of Erie County 1925-1931; elected as a Democrat to the Seventy-second, Seventy-third, and Seventy-fourth Congresses (March 4, 1931-January 3, 1937); unsuccessful candidate for renomination in 1936; resumed the practice of law in Sandusky, Ohio; died in Cleveland, Ohio, September 11, 1953; interment in Oakland Cemetery, Sandusky, Ohio.

researchRecord.name: 1900-1953, 2 linear feet.
researchRecord.description: The papers of William L. Fiesinger contain correspondence, subject files, clippings, and speeches covering Fiesinger's service in Congress and his subsequent years in law practice and retirement. Subjects focus on the economy and silver question, the collection also includes material on the Panama Canal. A finding aid is available in the repository and online.
